=== MUSICAL_LOCK ===
# id: 55
# title: The Musical Lock
# chinese_title: 音乐锁
# category: Puzzle
# mode: dungeon

A door's locking mechanism responds to sound frequencies. Musical notes are etched into the frame, each paired with a Chinese character indicating a tone. Your translator identifies them as the four tones of Mandarin. Play them in the right sequence, and the door opens.

* [Match the tones to the characters and play the sequence]
  ~ gain_radical("口")
  "唱" (chàng) — to sing. The radical "口" (kǒu) means mouth.
* [Record the frequencies and find the pattern]
  ~ gain_xp(20)
  "调" (diào) — tone, melody, to adjust
* [Force the door mechanism]
  ~ damage(5)
  "力" (lì) — force, strength
